President Cyril Ramaphosa is now expected to make his address on Monday. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa will no longer be addressing the nation on Sunday. Ramaphosa is now expected to make his address on Monday. The President is currently locked in a meeting with the National Command Council and the meeting is expected to go through the night. Earlier on Sunday, the president met with ministers and business about the effects of coronavirus on our country. The number of coronavirus cases in South Africa has risen to 240. Gauteng still has the most infections, with 16 new cases. Ramaphosa declared the coronavirus pandemic a national disaster. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs